article.headline: Seton Hall 65, Liberty 47
article.story: ANCHORAGE, Alaska (AP) -- Andre Barrett scored 28 points and had five assists and Seton Hall beat Liberty 65-47 on Saturday night to finish third in the Great Alaska Shootout. Barrett shot 9-for-19 from the field, including 5-for-11 from 3-point range. He also was 5-of-6 from the free-throw line. The Pirates (3-1) bolted to a 23-point first-half lead, but had to turn back a rally by the Flames late in the second. Liberty, which played No. 2 Duke even through most of the first half Friday, made just three field goals and four free throws and the Pirates took a 32-11 halftime lead. The Flames shot just 3-of-25 (12 percent) from the field in the half. Liberty recovered its shooting touch in the second half, opening with a 12-6 run behind six points by Louvon Sneed. The Flames closed to 43-35 with 8:51 remaining on a three-point play by Jason Sarchet, but could get no closer. Liberty shot 56 percent in the second half. Sarchet finished with 13 points and four rebounds. Marcus Tony-El had 12 points and five rebounds for Seton Hall. Andre Sweet had nine points and seven rebounds.
